 Near eastern, and classical Greek material, employing one of more of the four common approaches. This is the first volume devoted to applying memory studies to the "Deuteronomistic History."  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCollective memory. 0aDeuteronomistic history (Biblical criticism). 0aGroup identity. 4aDeuteronomistische Geschichte. 4aDeuteronomium. 4aKollektive Erinnerung. 4aKollektive Identität. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  aCollective Identity.  aCollective Memory.  aDeuteronomistic History.  aDeuteronomy.1 aBuster, Aubrey E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChau, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubovský, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdelman, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdelman, Diana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEdenburg, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilmour, Rachelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendel, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJürgensen, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevin, Yigal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkl, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiesiołowski-Spanò, Łukasz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerson, Raymond F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRüpke, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSano, Yoshinori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1